## 5. Code Organization Reference

```
clinical-signal/
├── apps/web/                 # Next.js — UI, API routes, Server Actions, lib/
│   ├── app/                  # App Router (RSC pages, api/, actions)
│   ├── lib/                  # Auth, patients, records, audit, __tests__/
│   ├── e2e/                  # Playwright ONLY
│   └── prompts/              # Version-controlled AI prompts (no PHI)
├── packages/
│   ├── core/src/             # TenantContext, roles, JWT, errors
│   └── db/src/               # withTenantContext, withSystem, phiKey, pool
├── services/analysis-engine/
│   ├── app/                  # FastAPI routes, pipeline, analyzer
│   ├── prompts/              # Engine prompts (no PHI)
│   └── tests/                # pytest
├── database/migrations/      # Numbered SQL migrations + RLS
└── docker-compose.yml        # Local dev stack
```

---

## 6. AI Change Discipline

1. **Read first:** Inspect related files (`lib/`, `@cs/db`, migrations, existing tests) before writing code.
2. **Minimal scope:** Smallest correct diff. No drive-by refactors or unrelated formatting.
3. **Security by default:** Every new PHI code path gets tenant context + RBAC + no plaintext logging.
4. **Test with the change:** Add/update Vitest or pytest tests in the same change set.
5. **Document non-obvious decisions** in code comments only when business logic or security rationale is not self-evident.
6. **MVP boundaries:** No patient portal, wearable integrations, billing, or multi-practitioner team features unless explicitly scoped.

---

## 7. Quick Reference — Security Anti-Patterns (NEVER DO)

- Query PHI tables with raw `pool.query()` or bare `psycopg.connect()` without tenant GUC
- Store patient name/DOB as plaintext in the database
- Log intake text, lab values, protocol content, or AI responses
- Expose PHI in Client Component state or browser storage
- Add mutating routes without `SessionUser.role` checks
- Import `withSystem` from non-allow-listed files
- Put real PHI in prompts, tests, seed data, or commit messages
- Use superuser DB credentials in web or analysis-engine runtime
- Skip Zod/Pydantic validation on external input
- Mix Playwright specs into Vitest runs

---

*These rules apply to all AI-assisted edits in this repository. Human reviewers enforce HIPAA compliance in production deployments.*
